A vast tree viewed from below, its trunk splitting into countless branches that further divide into intricate smaller limbs, each branch holding clusters of interconnected glowing orbs like neurons firing in a brain. The scene is rendered in Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures, warm amber and sage green tones, and a dreamy atmosphere. Some orbs drift freely between branches like dandelion seeds, representing ideas flowing between hierarchical and linear thought patterns. The perspective emphasizes both the structured vertical growth of the tree and the horizontal web-like connections between floating orbs. Dappled sunlight filters through the canopy creating pools of golden light. Small luminescent particles float in the air, suggesting the invisible pathways of human cognition and perception connecting disparate concepts into unified understanding.
